<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="522" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1370,2007]" pageId="1" pageNumber="522">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1370,1395]" pageId="1" pageNumber="522">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
General coloration greenish, with dark V-shaped spot at apex of crown; clypellus with dark spot of variable shape and size. 
<emphasis box="[421,479,1406,1431]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="522">Male</emphasis>
: connective Y-shaped; styles elongated and curved toward the midline; aedeagus long and thin, apex sharp, and basal portion Y-shaped.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="522" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1370,2007]" pageId="1" pageNumber="522">
<emphasis box="[199,418,1478,1503]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="522">Female terminalia.</emphasis>
Abdominal sternite VII, in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[911,983,1478,1503]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 20" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1759,1782]" captionTargetBox="[156,1418,242,1686]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1435,223,1686]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 20. Abdominal sternite VII (ventral view): 1 — Acrogonia citrina, 2 — Acrogonia virescens, 3 — Anacuerna centrolinea, 4 — Dechacona missionum, 5 — Diestostemma ptolyca, 6 — Egidemia speculifera, 7 — Homalodisca ignorata, 8 — Molomea cincta, 9 — Molomea confluens, 10 — Molomea consolida, 11 — Molomea lineiceps, 12 — Oncometopia expansa, 13 — Oncometopia facialis, 14 — Oncometopia tucumana, 15 — Oncometopia venata, 16 — Phera carbonaria, 17 — Tapajosa doeringi, 18 — Tapajosa rubromarginata, 19 — Tapajosa similis, 20 — Teletusa limpida. Scale: 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/244833/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="522">
Fig. 
<number box="[967,983,1479,1503]" pageId="1" pageNumber="522" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
), with lateral margins slightly parallel, lateroposterior margins broadly rounded, and posterior margin deeply emarginate bearing conspicuous median lobe inside emargination; with a few macrosetae at edges of emargination. Pygofer, in lateral view, slightly produced posteriorly; surface with scattered microsetae and macrosetae on posterior one-third of disc. First valvifers, in lateral view, longer than tall; with small spiniform processes in posterior one-third. First ovipositor valvulae, in lateral view, short and slightly rectilinear, basal portion expanded; dorsal sculptured area formed by scale-like processes arranged in oblique lines; ventral sculptured area formed by scale-like processes arranged irregularly; apex truncate with acute median projection (
<figureCitation box="[645,729,1730,1755]" captionStart="FIGURES 21 – 40" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1785,1808]" captionTargetBox="[153,1420,230,1727]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[153,1434,217,1731]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 21 – 40. First valvulae of ovipositor, apex (lateral view): 21 — Acrogonia citrina, 22 — Acrogonia virescens, 23 — Anacuerna centrolinea, 24 — Dechacona missionum, 25 — Diestostemma ptolyca, 26 — Egidemia speculifera, 27 — Homalodisca ignorata, 28 — Molomea cincta, 29 — Molomea confluens, 30 — Molomea consolida, 31 — Molomea lineiceps, 32 — Oncometopia expansa, 33 — Oncometopia facialis, 34 — Oncometopia tucumana, 35 — Oncometopia venata, 36 — Phera carbonaria, 37 — Tapajosa doeringi, 38 — Tapajosa rubromarginata, 39 — Tapajosa similis, 40 — Teletusa limpida. Scale: 0,1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/244834/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="522">
Fig. 
<number box="[697,729,1731,1755]" pageId="1" pageNumber="522" value="22.0">22</number>
</figureCitation>
). Second valvulae, in lateral view, short and slightly rectilinear; dorsal margin of blade bearing 
<number box="[506,600,1767,1791]" pageId="1" pageNumber="522" value="19.0" valueMax="20.0" valueMin="18.0">18 to 20</number>
noncontiguous teeth, each tooth subtriangular, declivous posteriorly, with denticles along entire dorsal margin (
<figureCitation box="[572,657,1802,1827]" captionStart="FIGURES 41 – 60" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1482,1505]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,240,1427]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[164,1422,229,1427]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 41 – 60. Second valvulae of ovipositor, teeth of dorsal margin (lateral view): 41 — Acrogonia citrina, 42 — Acrogonia virescens, 43 — Anacuerna centrolinea, 44 — Dechacona missionum, 45 — Diestostemma ptolyca, 46 — Egidemia speculifera, 47 — Homalodisca ignorata, 48 — Molomea cincta, 49 — Molomea confluens, 50 — Molomea consolida, 51 — Molomea lineiceps, 52 — Oncometopia expansa, 53 — Oncometopia facialis, 54 — Oncometopia tucumana, 55 — Oncometopia venata, 56 — Phera carbonaria, 57 — Tapajosa doeringi, 58 — Tapajosa rubromarginata, 59 — Tapajosa similis, 60 — Teletusa limpida. Scale: 0,1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/244835/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="522">
Fig. 
<number box="[625,657,1803,1827]" pageId="1" pageNumber="522" value="42.0">42</number>
</figureCitation>
); size of teeth increases from proximal portion to middle region, and then decreases towards apex, ducts extending toward teeth and toward apical blade portion; apex obtuse, forming a concavity with preapical ventral prominence (
<figureCitation box="[684,773,1874,1899]" captionStart="FIGURES 61 – 80" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1797,1820]" captionTargetBox="[156,1416,231,1733]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[156,1430,217,1745]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 61 – 80. Second valvulae of ovipositor, apex (lateral view): 61 — Acrogonia citrina, 62 — Acrogonia virescens, 63 — Anacuerna centrolinea, 64 — Dechacona missionum, 65 — Diestostemma ptolyca, 66 — Egidemia speculifera, 67 — Homalodisca ignorata, 68 — Molomea cincta, 69 — Molomea confluens, 70 — Molomea consolida, 71 — Molomea lineiceps, 72 — Oncometopia expansa, 73 — Oncometopia facialis, 74 — Oncometopia tucumana, 75 — Oncometopia venata, 76 — Phera carbonaria, 77 — Tapajosa doeringi, 78 — Tapajosa rubromarginata, 79 — Tapajosa similis, 80 — Teletusa limpida. Scale: 0,1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/244836/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="522">
Fig. 
<number box="[741,773,1874,1899]" pageId="1" pageNumber="522" value="62.0">62</number>
</figureCitation>
). Gonoplacs, in lateral view, with basal half narrow, and apical half short and distinctly expanded; apex acute.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
